  "text": "neuroprotective [CITATION_1] . Likewise, 6-OHDA increased autophagy, ROS, and apoptotic cell death in SH-SY5Y cells, and inhibiting macroautophagy with 3-MA or an AMPK inhibiting neurotrophic factor ameliorated these deficits and increased cell viability [CITATION_2] . MPP+ similarly increased macroautophagy and markers of PCD in SH-SY5Y cells, and expression of AMPK-DN attenuated these effects, while 3-MA prevented cell death as measured by LDH release [CITATION_3] . In both primary neurons and PC12 cells, administration of 6-OHDA, rotenone, or MPP+ each increased AMPK activity, decreased cell viability, and promoted apoptosis. Cell viability was improved by inhibiting AMPK with compound C, expressing AMPK-DN, or by inhibiting macroautophagy through overexpression of mTORC1 [CITATION_4] .",
